# Code Style Guidelines

## General Rules

### 1. Strict TypeScript Type Safety

- Use explicit type declarations
- Avoid using `any` type
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object type definitions

### 2. Code Formatting

- Use Tab indentation (following biome.json config)
- Use double quotes for strings
- Enable automatic import sorting
- Follow Biome's recommended rules

### 3. File and Directory Structure

- Use kebab-case for file and directory naming
- Use PascalCase.tsx for component files
- Use `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx` for test files
- Use index.ts for export files

### 4. English Comments

- All function comments (JSDoc) must be written in English
- Inline comments should be in English
- Documentation and README files should be in English
- Variable and function names remain in English following naming conventions

### 5. Error Messages and Runtime Prompts

- All runtime error messages must be in English
- All console.log, console.warn, console.error messages must be in English
- All throw new Error() messages must be in English
- All user-facing prompts and notifications must be in English
- Only code comments and documentation can be in English

### 6. Early Return Pattern

- **Functions should prefer early returns** to reduce nesting and improve code readability
- Return early for edge cases and invalid conditions
- Use continue in loops when conditions are met early
- Avoid deep nesting by handling special cases first
- Extract complex conditional logic into separate methods when appropriate
- Extract complex conditions into descriptive variables for better readability
- Prefer early return over nested if-else statements

## Import and Export Rules

- Use explicit imports (avoid `import *`)
- Organize imports: external packages first, then internal modules
- Use index.ts files for clean public APIs
- Avoid circular dependencies
- Use type-only imports when appropriate (`import type`)

## Error Handling

- Always handle errors explicitly
- Provide meaningful error messages in English
- Use appropriate error types (Error, TypeError, etc.)
- Log errors appropriately (avoid console.log except for errors)
- Fail fast with clear error messages

## Prohibited Practices

- Don't modify dist directory directly
- Don't use console.log in code (except for error handling)
- Don't bypass TypeScript type checking
- Don't use @ts-ignore in production code
